Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.63,0:00:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good morning everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.52,0:00:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to session 206,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.34,0:00:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Introducing Password Autofill
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.22,0:00:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,for Apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.60,0:00:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Ricky Mondello.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.71,0:00:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I am thrilled to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.25,0:00:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,tell you about Password
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.38,0:00:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Autofill, a new feature in iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.17,0:00:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,11 that puts passwords that your
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,users have already saved in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.15,0:00:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari and in iCloud Keychain
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.20,0:00:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,directly on the keyboard within
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.83,0:00:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps to make logging in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.03,0:00:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,super simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.54,0:00:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We made Password Autofill
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.92,0:01:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because logging into apps is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.20,0:01:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.30,0:01:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a source of friction.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.29,0:01:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, when I've downloaded
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.24,0:01:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a new app from the Store and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.88,0:01:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen the login screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.74,0:01:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes I've just switched
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.28,0:01:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,back to Safari where I knew I
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.06,0:01:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,was already logged into the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.15,0:01:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,app's website.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.80,0:01:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But beyond an inconvenience for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.22,0:01:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,me, for so many people any
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.58,0:01:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,experience dealing with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.65,0:01:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords is a source of real
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.52,0:01:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,frustration or even panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.97,0:01:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So the truth is, although having
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.85,0:01:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to log into your apps is really
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.23,0:01:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,important, it is a source of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.93,0:01:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,friction that can lead to users
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.32,0:01:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,abandoning your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.87,0:01:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And none of us want that to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.88,0:01:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.40,0:01:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You make awesome apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.85,0:01:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We want users to use them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.21,0:01:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, in iOS 11 Password
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.42,0:01:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Autofill can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.31,0:01:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.43,0:01:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS and MacOS have a password
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.18,0:01:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,manager that's built in,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.43,0:01:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,integrated into Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.99,0:01:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've probably seen it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.15,0:01:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,before.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.08,0:01:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're logging into a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.32,0:02:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,website, it offers to save your
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.23,0:02:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.44,0:02:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next time that you come
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.91,0:02:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,back to that website, it fills
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.11,0:02:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,them automatically for you to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.83,0:02:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,make logging in really easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.68,0:02:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want you to know that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.80,0:02:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari takes the security of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.46,0:02:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,users' passwords extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.93,0:02:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.56,0:02:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user has saved a password
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.14,0:02:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for your website, Safari will
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.44,0:02:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,only ever fill that password on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.33,0:02:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,your website.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.08,0:02:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Passwords for your website won't
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.72,0:02:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,be offered on any other
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.89,0:02:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,websites.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.01,0:02:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, if the user wants
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.11,0:02:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to look up one of their
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.10,0:02:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords on a device, viewing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.90,0:02:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the passwords requires them to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.14,0:02:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,authenticate, either with Touch
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.06,0:02:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ID or with their passcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.82,0:02:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The point is, iOS keeps these
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.24,0:02:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords secure on device.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.48,0:02:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, iOS synchs all of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.35,0:02:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,these passwords across a user's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.91,0:02:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,devices using iCloud Keychain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.67,0:02:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And this makes it super easy to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.95,0:02:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,log in across multiple devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.29,0:03:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And this, too, is secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.36,0:03:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We actually have a really
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.45,0:03:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,approachable white paper on
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.22,0:03:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple.com that describes the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.30,0:03:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,security model of iCloud
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.09,0:03:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Keychain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.02,0:03:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And it goes into a great amount
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.32,0:03:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of detail about how and why
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.37,0:03:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple cannot see a user's
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.94,0:03:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,synched passwords, but it still
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.99,0:03:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,makes them available on all the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.50,0:03:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.70,0:03:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari AutoFill and iCloud
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.67,0:03:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Keychain are built directly into
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.49,0:03:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS and MacOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.34,0:03:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari AutoFill is enabled by
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.27,0:03:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,default for all users.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.57,0:03:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And every user is prompted to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.99,0:03:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,turn on iCloud Keychain when
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.02,0:03:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,they set up a new device.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.46,0:03:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,These features are extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.66,0:03:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.78,0:03:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of your users have
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.04,0:03:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords saved in iCloud
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.38,0:03:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Keychain and Safari AutoFill.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.93,0:03:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And what iOS 11 does is it takes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.53,0:03:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,these passwords that already
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,saved in the Keychain and makes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.14,0:03:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,them available on the keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.11,0:03:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,within your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.90,0:03:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think the best way to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.76,0:04:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,understand this is to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.69,0:04:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's start off with a demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.44,0:04:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what I have right here is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.57,0:04:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Shiny, which is a demo app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.39,0:04:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's personally my favorite
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.96,0:04:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,demo app for logging in and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.93,0:04:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing a picture of something
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.11,0:04:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that's pleasant every single
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.22,0:04:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.43,0:04:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to open up this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.37,0:04:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.33,0:04:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has a very standard login
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.10,0:04:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,screen, like many of your apps
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.52,0:04:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,do, with a username and a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.25,0:04:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,password field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So like any user would, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.37,0:04:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,going to tap into the username
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.86,0:04:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.70,0:04:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the first things
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.49,0:04:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll probably notice is that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.39,0:04:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,directly above the keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.58,0:04:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the QuickType bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.10,0:04:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the QuickType bar is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.08,0:04:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,offering my password from the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,website for Shiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And with one tap, that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,information is filled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.29,0:04:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And with another tap, I'm logged
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.67,0:04:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.92,0:04:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an adorable puppy, 13 out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.82,0:04:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.37,0:04:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's do that one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.58,0:04:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It went by pretty quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.17,0:05:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This time I'll just happen to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.34,0:05:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,touch into the password field.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.46,0:05:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm offered the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.18,0:05:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tap and tap.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.44,0:05:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm logged in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.99,0:05:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Another good dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.74,0:05:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So one thing I want to point out
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.93,0:05:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,while I'm showing you this is I
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.14,0:05:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned a moment ago that iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.41,0:05:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,takes password security very
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.10,0:05:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.02,0:05:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the big thing to notice
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.22,0:05:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,here is iOS isn't guessing that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,shiny.example.com is the website
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.68,0:05:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Shiny app.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.07,0:05:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a strong two-way secure
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.33,0:05:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,association between that app and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.16,0:05:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that website that allows iOS to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.27,0:05:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,put the exact right credential
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.76,0:05:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that the user's looking for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.11,0:05:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,right on the QuickType bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.21,0:05:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.79,0:05:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to some slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.13,0:05:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You just saw that iOS 11 put the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.79,0:05:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,password that I needed to log
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.45,0:05:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,into Shiny directly on the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.34,0:05:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,QuickType bar above the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.33,0:05:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard, which made logging in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.40,0:06:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as simple as two taps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.60,0:06:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I have no reason to abandon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.90,0:06:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the app and go back to Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.47,0:06:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,where I was already logged in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.11,0:06:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as easy to log into
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.24,0:06:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick show of hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of you have a screen in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.40,0:06:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,your app that looks like this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.55,0:06:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,one with a username and a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.63,0:06:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,password field?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.64,0:06:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.30,0:06:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lot of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.15,0:06:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're all in the right
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.02,0:06:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one more show of hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.40,0:06:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of those apps are you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.43,0:06:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,logging into your own backend
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.79,0:06:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that you manage yourself instead
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.42,0:06:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of a third party service?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.73,0:06:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.30,0:06:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lot of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.93,0:06:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,For everyone who kept their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.15,0:06:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,up, who raised it a second time,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.78,0:06:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to be talking to you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.96,0:06:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout most of this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.70,0:06:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.35,0:06:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're logging into a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.26,0:06:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,third party service like a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.66,0:06:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,social network, I'll have a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.76,0:06:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,little something for you toward
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.83,0:06:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.31,0:06:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We want Password AutoFill to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.22,0:06:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,work for as many of your apps as
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.82,0:06:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.08,0:06:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we built heuristics into iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.84,0:07:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that make some parts of Password
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.46,0:07:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,AutoFill work automatically in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.63,0:07:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,many apps without you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.24,0:07:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,necessarily having to change
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.63,0:07:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.43,0:07:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,However, for your users to get
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.49,0:07:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the best experience where the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.27,0:07:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,exact right credential shows up
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.22,0:07:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,on the QuickType bar, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.67,0:07:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,going to need a little bit of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.46,0:07:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.82,0:07:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we're going to focus on
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.92,0:07:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for the rest of this session is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.61,0:07:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,guaranteeing that your apps get
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.59,0:07:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience that you just saw
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.26,0:07:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Shiny app.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.85,0:07:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll do that by walking
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.43,0:07:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,through these topics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.70,0:07:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The first topic is about making
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.71,0:07:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the QuickType bar appear in your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.67,0:07:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,username and password fields in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.37,0:07:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.03,0:07:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The second is about making sure
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.03,0:07:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that the passwords are filled
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.33,0:07:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,properly into the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.30,0:07:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And that your app works properly
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.13,0:07:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,after a user taps on one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.37,0:07:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,suggestions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.20,0:07:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll talk about making
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.85,0:07:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,sure that the exact right
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.30,0:07:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,credential that your user is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.54,0:07:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for, the credential from
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,your website, shows up on the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:07:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,left-hand side of the QuickType
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.03,0:07:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.35,0:07:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at the end, we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.91,0:08:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,circle back around and talk
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.09,0:08:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,about authenticating against a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.60,0:08:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,third party service, a service
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not the same as your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.62,0:08:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's get started by talking
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.65,0:08:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,about making the QuickType bar
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.05,0:08:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.60,0:08:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing to know about
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.90,0:08:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the QuickType bar appearing is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.72,0:08:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that it will only appear if you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.33,0:08:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,have at least one saved password
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.91,0:08:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,on an iOS device.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.74,0:08:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need for us to offer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.82,0:08:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Password AutoFill if there are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.00,0:08:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,no passwords to fill.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.13,0:08:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing to know is that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.93,0:08:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,UITextView and UITextField are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.99,0:08:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically eligible for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.49,0:08:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,consideration or Password
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.28,0:08:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,AutoFill.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.02,0:08:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're using these
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.72,0:08:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,standard controls out of UIKit,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.06,0:08:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you're already in a really good
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.17,0:08:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.98,0:08:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you're rolling your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.10,0:08:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,own text fields, no need to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.82,0:08:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If your text field conforms to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.13,0:08:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,UITextInput, it's also eligible
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.67,0:08:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for Password Autofill.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.21,0:08:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And I mentioned this earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.79,0:08:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but iOS is going to use
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.13,0:09:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,heuristics to determine where to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.48,0:09:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,show the QuickType bar in your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.39,0:09:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,username and your password
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.51,0:09:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.34,0:09:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And iOS's heuristics are pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.18,0:09:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.05,0:09:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But what we're here to do is to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.82,0:09:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,guarantee that your app has
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.64,0:09:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Password AutoFill.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.15,0:09:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can guarantee that by
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.62,0:09:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,having you tell iOS which of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.08,0:09:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,your fields is the username
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.06,0:09:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,field and which is the password
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.52,0:09:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,field.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.40,0:09:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way that we'll do this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.08,0:09:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is through UITextContentType.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.50,0:09:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,By setting a content type on the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.47,0:09:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,text fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.50,0:09:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,UITextContentType was introduced
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.01,0:09:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,as an optional property on the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.90,0:09:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,UITextInputTraits protocol in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.36,0:09:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.53,0:09:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS uses it to have a better
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.91,0:09:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of what
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.44,0:09:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,information is in your text
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.70,0:09:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could imagine that iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.06,0:09:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,would offer a different and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.08,0:09:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,better keyboard or auto
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.67,0:09:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,corrections if it knew that your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.41,0:09:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,users was typing an email
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.58,0:09:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,address versus, say, their last
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.42,0:09:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.70,0:10:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are the text content types
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.57,0:10:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that are present in iOS 10, just
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.90,0:10:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to give you a refresher.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.04,0:10:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you've probably guessed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.62,0:10:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in iOS 11 there are two new text
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.05,0:10:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,content types, username and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.96,0:10:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,password, that you can tag your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.42,0:10:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,fields with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.34,0:10:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So to guarantee that Password
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.53,0:10:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,AutoFill is working in your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.04,0:10:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,apps, we're going to deploy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.71,0:10:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,UITextContentType.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.90,0:10:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to be our guarantee
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that Password AutoFill is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.40,0:10:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,available in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.44,0:10:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can set text content types
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.21,0:10:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,from within code.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.66,0:10:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, with an interface filter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.53,0:10:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll show you how to do
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.36,0:10:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that in a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.62,0:10:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The username text content type
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.15,0:10:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is particularly useful if your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.08,0:10:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,app has a two-screen login
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.67,0:10:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,experience where your username
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.65,0:10:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,field is on a different view or
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.57,0:10:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,screen than your password.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.12,0:10:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, if you tag your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.93,0:10:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,username field with the username
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.47,0:10:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,text content type, we'll be able
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.28,0:11:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to offer the QuickType bar on
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.87,0:11:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,both of the screens.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.42,0:11:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're already using the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.12,0:11:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,email address text content type,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.45,0:11:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.02,0:11:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You can combine the username
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.87,0:11:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,text content type and the email
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.91,0:11:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard to give your users the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.64,0:11:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,best of both worlds, where they
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.98,0:11:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,get an email address keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.85,0:11:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and QuickType Autofill.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.68,0:11:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The password text content type
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.03,0:11:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is particularly useful if you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.59,0:11:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,have a feature in your app that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.83,0:11:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,reveals the password that the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.43,0:11:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,user is typing in plain text to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.03,0:11:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,help them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.88,0:11:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When your field is in plain text
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.07,0:11:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS won't be able to tell that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.22,0:11:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a password field unless you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.87,0:11:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,tag the field as a password.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.00,0:11:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you do that, the QuickType
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.47,0:11:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,bar will still work in that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.53,0:11:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,field, even when it's not a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.93,0:11:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,secure entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.28,0:11:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And at this point, once you've
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.46,0:11:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,done this, you might see a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.17,0:11:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Password AutoFill QuickType bar
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.98,0:12:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in your app with its key icon on
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.38,0:12:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the right, but without any
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.12,0:12:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,specific credentials showing up
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.66,0:12:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.02,0:12:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is actually expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.20,0:12:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a really good first
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.28,0:12:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,step.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.32,0:12:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In a little bit we'll talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.79,0:12:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,making your website's passwords
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.59,0:12:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,show up on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.66,0:12:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But what seeing this bar means
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.80,0:12:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is that iOS is ready to offer
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.51,0:12:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Password AutoFill.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.52,0:12:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And if users tap on that key on
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.21,0:12:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the right-hand side, they'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.18,0:12:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,able to authenticate using Touch
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.86,0:12:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,ID and see a list of their
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.53,0:12:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords that they can search
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.31,0:12:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,through or scroll through in
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.83,0:12:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,order to fill one of those
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.78,0:12:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords within your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.22,0:12:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And once they've found the right
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.34,0:12:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,password, and they tap it, iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.28,0:12:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,will fill that information into
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.96,0:12:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,your fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.98,0:12:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Which brings us to our next
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.25,0:12:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,topic, which is ensuring the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,information that's filled into
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.07,0:12:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,your text fields is understood
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.61,0:12:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,by your app and that users able
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.56,0:12:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to log in successfully
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.94,0:12:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.23,0:12:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS is going to do its best to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.93,0:12:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,put information into your
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.14,0:13:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,username and password fields in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.08,0:13:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a very similar way to how users
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.60,0:13:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would type that information
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.72,0:13:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.24,0:13:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's still a good idea to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.35,0:13:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,test that your app behaves
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.72,0:13:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,properly after information has
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.45,0:13:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,been autofilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.26,0:13:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What we want to see is that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.97,0:13:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,users are able to just tap your
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.32,0:13:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,sign-in button and log directly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.00,0:13:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.86,0:13:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's talk about what you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.95,0:13:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,need to know about how Password
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.37,0:13:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,AutoFill fills into your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.50,0:13:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing is something
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.93,0:13:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you've already seen, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.79,0:13:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that iOS will fill both the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.20,0:13:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,username and the password fields
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.38,0:13:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in a single gesture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.50,0:13:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS will change your app's first
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.15,0:13:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,responder in order to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.30,0:13:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS is going to do this even if
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.42,0:13:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,your app prevents changing the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.83,0:13:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,first responder at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.98,0:13:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're doing something
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.89,0:13:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,like this, it's worth knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.05,0:13:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A moment ago I showed you the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.02,0:13:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,flow where a user taps on the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.32,0:13:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,key icon and Touch ID comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.97,0:13:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And when Touch ID appears, your
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.81,0:13:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,app will become inactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.05,0:14:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's worth knowing because
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.11,0:14:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it leads directly into our first
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.06,0:14:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,best practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.72,0:14:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is that when Touch ID
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.53,0:14:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,appears, there's no need for you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.50,0:14:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to tear down your login UI or
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.27,0:14:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,hide it when your app becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.04,0:14:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,inactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.97,0:14:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you do this, all a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.49,0:14:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,user is going to see is tapping
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,on the key, finding the right
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.80,0:14:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,password and tapping it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.68,0:14:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then iOS isn't going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.22,0:14:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,able to fill anything because
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.54,0:14:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the text fields will have
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.58,0:14:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.24,0:14:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it might be a good idea to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.34,0:14:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,hide sensitive information in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.04,0:14:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,your app when your app becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.44,0:14:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,inactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.79,0:14:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But if a user actually hasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.07,0:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,finished logging in yet, that's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.60,0:14:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,probably not necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You might have buttons in your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.57,0:14:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,app, like a login button or a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.63,0:14:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,sign-in button, that only lights
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.47,0:14:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,up and enables itself once
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.12,0:14:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,there's actually information
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.59,0:14:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,filled into the username and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,password field.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.73,0:14:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best practice here is to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.93,0:14:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,us did change notifications or
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.38,0:14:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,delegate methods to revalidate
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.20,0:14:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,those buttons whenever the text
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.77,0:14:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.82,0:15:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're using UITextField,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.91,0:15:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a notification that you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.05,0:15:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,can use.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.28,0:15:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're using UITextView,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.85,0:15:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a notification and a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.03,0:15:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,delegate method.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.64,0:15:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're rolling your own
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.63,0:15:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,custom text input, if you can
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.06,0:15:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,form the UITextInputDelegate,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.32,0:15:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a delegate method that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.31,0:15:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you can listen to again to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.97,0:15:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,revalidate your buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.65,0:15:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you're doing that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.21,0:15:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,validation, you should read
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.14,0:15:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,information directly from your
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.30,0:15:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,text field's text property.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.78,0:15:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,UIKit makes it incredibly cheap
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.36,0:15:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to read information out of a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.69,0:15:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,text field.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.61,0:15:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's always accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.54,0:15:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do this, you'll eliminate
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.84,0:15:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,categorically an entire class of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.57,0:15:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,bugs that you can have with
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.65,0:15:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,cash-in validation based on what
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.67,0:15:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,information is entered into your
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.15,0:15:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,text fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.38,0:15:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.63,0:15:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a few best practices
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.32,0:15:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for ensuring that after a user
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.25,0:15:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,has used AutoFill, that your app
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.90,0:16:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is able to login successfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.75,0:16:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And users can go about their
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.83,0:16:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,business.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.30,0:16:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Which brings us to our third
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.15,0:16:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,topic, which is making sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.83,0:16:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the QuickType bar is showing the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.49,0:16:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,exact right credentials for your
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.96,0:16:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,website.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.37,0:16:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So at this point in your testing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.15,0:16:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you might still have what we saw
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.41,0:16:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,earlier, which is a bar with a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.63,0:16:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,key on it, but without any
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.09,0:16:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,specific credentials on the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.27,0:16:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.78,0:16:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you know, in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.07,0:16:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,give users the best experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.42,0:16:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the one that is most going to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.84,0:16:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,reduce the odds that they
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.22,0:16:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,abandon your app, we'll want the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.96,0:16:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,exact correct credentials
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.37,0:16:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,showing up on the QuickType bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.19,0:16:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I touched on this briefly
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.62,0:16:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,during the demo earlier, but
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.56,0:16:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Password AutoFill will only put
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.26,0:16:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,credentials on the QuickType bar
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.17,0:16:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,when it is safe to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.79,0:16:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.78,0:16:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS is not guessing what
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.11,0:16:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,websites are affiliated with
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.93,0:16:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,your app to find out which
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.47,0:16:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords are correct for your
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.25,0:16:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.43,0:16:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.17,0:17:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you've adopted universal
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.21,0:17:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,links, that feature that can
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.81,0:17:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,open up links when a user taps
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.47,0:17:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,on them inside of your app,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.37,0:17:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than opening them up in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.71,0:17:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari, if you've done that, you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.97,0:17:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,might actually already see that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.78,0:17:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS understands that your app
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.27,0:17:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and your website are associated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.82,0:17:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And it'll put the right
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.98,0:17:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,credentials on the QuickType
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.26,0:17:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.06,0:17:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you haven't adopted
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.42,0:17:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,universal links, or it doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.98,0:17:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,really make sense for you to do
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.11,0:17:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so, there's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.43,0:17:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a dedicated technology
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.39,0:17:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to linking your app and your
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.51,0:17:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,website together strongly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.77,0:17:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to walk you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.59,0:17:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.06,0:17:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In this diagram it's your app on
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.69,0:17:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.23,0:17:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the right is your web
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.37,0:17:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,server or your backend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.27,0:17:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ideas is that your app,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.82,0:17:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,through its signed entitlements,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.16,0:17:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,says what website or websites it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.10,0:17:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is affiliated with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.93,0:17:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And whenever your app is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.02,0:17:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,installed or iOS installs an
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.99,0:17:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,update, iOS is going to check
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.36,0:18:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with that domain at a particular
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.64,0:18:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,file path to see, to look for
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,some information.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.58,0:18:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't know the well-known
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.70,0:18:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,directory, it's just a standard
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.40,0:18:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,place to put files for
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.55,0:18:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,information discovery, like the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.42,0:18:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,file I'm about to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.38,0:18:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.68,0:18:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple-app-site-association.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.38,0:18:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS will only ever attempt to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.90,0:18:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,fetch this file over HTTPS, over
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.03,0:18:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a secure connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.36,0:18:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In response to that request,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.72,0:18:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,your website can return a JSON
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.00,0:18:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,response.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.35,0:18:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that JSON response is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.89,0:18:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,formatted properly, what it can
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.61,0:18:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,say is: Here is the list of apps
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.94,0:18:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm associated with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.65,0:18:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the app points to the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.12,0:18:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,website, and the website points
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.90,0:18:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,right back to the app, boom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.14,0:18:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a secure two-way link.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.40,0:18:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So to put what I've told you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.55,0:18:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,about so far into practice,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.80,0:18:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly with establishing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.42,0:18:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,this secure connection between
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.30,0:19:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,your app and your website, I am
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.37,0:19:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,delighted to invite my colleague
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.22,0:19:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Maureen Daum to the stage to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.04,0:19:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,give you a demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.35,0:19:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Maureen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.52,0:19:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.38,0:19:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks Ricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.40,0:19:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here I have the Shiny app
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.01,0:19:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,before we've done any work to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.90,0:19:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,make Password AutoFill work with
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.81,0:19:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.08,0:19:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I tap in the username
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.59,0:19:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,field, iOS automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.57,0:19:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,detected that this is in fact
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.61,0:19:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the username field.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.49,0:19:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And it gives us the Password
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.32,0:19:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,AutoFill QuickType bar -- thank
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.52,0:19:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you -- for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.36,0:19:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So now users, if they don't
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.00,0:19:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,remember their credentials, can
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.06,0:19:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,tap on the Key icon,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.87,0:19:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,authenticate with Touch ID and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.64,0:19:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,find the right credential.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.33,0:19:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.56,0:19:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a great experience
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.42,0:19:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for my users that might not
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.98,0:19:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,remember their credentials.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.45,0:19:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I really want to make
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.99,0:19:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it even easier for them to log
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.09,0:20:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in is to have those credentials
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.14,0:20:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,show up right on the QuickType
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.91,0:20:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.32,0:20:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to do two things in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.80,0:20:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,this demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.02,0:20:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is to guarantee that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.10,0:20:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we get this password QuickType
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.84,0:20:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,bar instead of just relying on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.88,0:20:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the heuristics.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.32,0:20:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second thing is to get
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.46,0:20:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the right credentials on the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.83,0:20:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,QuickType bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.09,0:20:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's do that first step,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.89,0:20:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,guaranteeing that we get the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.42,0:20:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,credentials.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.66,0:20:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,To do this, I'm going to tag my
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.58,0:20:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,username and password fields
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.56,0:20:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,with the right content type.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.85,0:20:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's my username field.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.06,0:20:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've already set its content
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.13,0:20:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,type to email address, because
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.34,0:20:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,some of my usernames might be
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.11,0:20:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,email addresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.50,0:20:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I switch this to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.72,0:20:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,username, down here at the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.09,0:20:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom, I can set the keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.22,0:20:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,type to email address.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.29,0:20:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So go down here the keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.74,0:20:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,type and set that one to email.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.63,0:20:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So now if the user has to type
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.57,0:20:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in their username, they'll still
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.28,0:20:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,get the right keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.36,0:20:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I'll go to password and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.06,0:20:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,set that content type to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.58,0:21:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,password, all the way at the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.33,0:21:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.23,0:21:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to rerun this just
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.11,0:21:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to verify that we still get the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.74,0:21:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,QuickType bar showing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.70,0:21:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't expect anything to have
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.17,0:21:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,changed because iOS was already
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.60,0:21:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,detecting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.42,0:21:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's good to make sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.91,0:21:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, once the login screen
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.82,0:21:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,comes up, we can tap in and we
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.34,0:21:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,still get the QuickType bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.72,0:21:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.15,0:21:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, to get the credentials
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.48,0:21:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,showing up, we need to tell iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.49,0:21:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that our app and our website are
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.46,0:21:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,associated.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.59,0:21:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do this, we'll adopt the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.50,0:21:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,web credentials associated
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.78,0:21:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,domain service.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.65,0:21:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to do this, the first step,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.33,0:21:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is to make our app tell iOS what
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.62,0:21:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,websites it's associated with.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.30,0:21:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go here to the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Capabilities tab in our app and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.42,0:21:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,turn on Associated Domains.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.71,0:21:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I have the ability to add
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.73,0:22:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,domains that my app is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.46,0:22:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,associated with.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.26,0:22:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So click the Plus button and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.14,0:22:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode as a placeholder domain
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.87,0:22:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.63,0:22:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So it has the web credentials
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.84,0:22:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,:prefix, because we're using the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.77,0:22:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,web credential service.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.53,0:22:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you will replace
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.25,0:22:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,example.com with the domain your
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.89,0:22:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,app is associated with.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.75,0:22:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So my app is associated with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.50,0:22:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Shiny.example.com.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.10,0:22:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you add a domain, Xcode
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.68,0:22:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,will do two things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.49,0:22:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is it adds an
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.20,0:22:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,entitlement to your entitlements
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.98,0:22:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,file so that when your app is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.78,0:22:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,installed iOS will look at this
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.26,0:22:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,list of domains and go to each
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.32,0:22:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,one of them to find the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.08,0:22:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple-App-Site-Association file.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.89,0:22:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The second thing it does is it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.59,0:22:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,makes sure that your app has
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.81,0:22:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,associated domains enabled.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.47,0:22:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So if your app ID does not have
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.61,0:22:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this enabled, you won't see a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.25,0:22:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,checkmark next to this second
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.97,0:22:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.49,0:23:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It will have an error.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.74,0:23:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you see an error there,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.47,0:23:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really easy to fix.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.33,0:23:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You just need to go to the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.50,0:23:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Developer Portal, select your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.68,0:23:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,app ID, and turn on Associated
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.83,0:23:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Domains.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.92,0:23:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it will be fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.99,0:23:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is all we had to do to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.51,0:23:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,tell iOS that our app is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.98,0:23:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,associated with our website.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.62,0:23:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we need to make our
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.59,0:23:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,website agree and point back to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.21,0:23:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,our app so that iOS can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.79,0:23:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,establish the two-way link.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.73,0:23:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So to do this, I'll create an
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.31,0:23:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple App Site association file.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.57,0:23:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's some JSON that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.11,0:23:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,specifies we're using the web
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.50,0:23:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,credential service, which
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.33,0:23:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,matches what we saw in Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.04,0:23:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Then within this dictionary is a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.74,0:23:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,list of all the app IDs of the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.30,0:23:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,apps our website is associated
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.22,0:23:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.13,0:23:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And my website only knows about
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.88,0:23:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the Shiny app.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.35,0:23:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So its app ID consists of the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.51,0:23:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Team Identifier, which you can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.89,0:24:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,find on the Developer Portal,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.11,0:24:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,followed by a period, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.45,0:24:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,your bundle identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.68,0:24:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's save that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.20,0:24:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I need to get it onto my
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,server.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.18,0:24:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And this step might look
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.95,0:24:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,different for you depending on
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.30,0:24:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,how your website is set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.15,0:24:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm just going to use SCP to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.39,0:24:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,copy it up there, to the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.88,0:24:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,.well-known subdirectory.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.34,0:24:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Great. So it's up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.45,0:24:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then just to double check,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.07,0:24:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go into Safari and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.55,0:24:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,visit the site that iOS is going
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.72,0:24:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.76,0:24:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's HTTPS
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.01,0:24:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Shiny.example.com/.well-known/
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.56,0:24:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,apple-app-site-association.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.73,0:24:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I go there, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.18,0:24:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the JSON recreated.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.38,0:24:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't see any smart
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.11,0:24:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,quotes, which could cause the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.87,0:24:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,JSON to be malformed and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.79,0:24:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore it wouldn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.49,0:24:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it looks like we're all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.76,0:24:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We've set up our app to point to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.14,0:24:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,our website.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.19,0:25:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Our website to point to our app.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.70,0:25:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's rerun this and see that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.20,0:25:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we get the credentials we want
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.12,0:25:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,showing up on the QuickType bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.75,0:25:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you're testing this on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.01,0:25:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps, make sure to test it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.03,0:25:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on a device, because Associated
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.16,0:25:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Domains is a device-only
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.92,0:25:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.98,0:25:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we are back in our app.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.84,0:25:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I tap in the username field.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.37,0:25:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Great! We have the credentials
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.40,0:25:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,right there on the QuickType
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.90,0:25:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.73,0:25:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So my users can tap, fill them
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.54,0:25:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in, one more tap, and then they
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.20,0:25:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,get to see a really adorable
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.60,0:25:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,puppy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.81,0:25:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how easy it is to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.12,0:25:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,guarantee that Password AutoFill
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.35,0:25:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,will work in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.97,0:25:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And that the credentials your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.38,0:25:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,users need will show up on the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.58,0:25:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,QuickType bar to get them logged
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.55,0:25:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in really quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.07,0:25:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I'll hand it back over to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.38,0:25:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ricky to tell you more.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.52,0:25:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.26,0:25:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, Maureen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.16,0:25:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That was really cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.70,0:26:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Maureen just showed you just how
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.99,0:26:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,easy it is to set text content
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.23,0:26:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,types from within Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.82,0:26:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She also showed you how to add
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.69,0:26:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the web credentials associated
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.67,0:26:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,domain capability in your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.74,0:26:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Capabilities tab.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.31,0:26:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And she told you that that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.30,0:26:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,capability gets signed into your
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.84,0:26:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,app's binary.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.23,0:26:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you need to enable the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.29,0:26:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,associated domains feature on
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.06,0:26:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the Developer Portal, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.70,0:26:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,really easy to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.92,0:26:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.92,0:26:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you navigate to the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.75,0:26:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Developer Portal.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.38,0:26:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And from there you can click on
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.19,0:26:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Certificates, Identifiers and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.26,0:26:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Profiles, either in the side bar
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.58,0:26:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or in the main content area.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.87,0:26:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And from there you can select
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.07,0:26:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,App IDs and look at a list of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.73,0:26:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,app IDs that are associated with
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.34,0:26:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,your developer account.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.21,0:26:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And from there, if you select
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.89,0:26:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the app ID that you'd like to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.69,0:26:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,modify, you'll see a list of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.64,0:26:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,services that can be enabled for
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.25,0:26:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.52,0:26:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And from there you can click the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.54,0:26:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Edit button and check the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.81,0:27:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Associated Domains checkbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.97,0:27:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.65,0:27:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You also saw just how easy it is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.87,0:27:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to construct an
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.57,0:27:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple-App-Site-Association that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.81,0:27:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,points back to your app from
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.28,0:27:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,your website.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.44,0:27:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a few lines of JSON.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.82,0:27:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Maureen then uploaded that JSON
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.82,0:27:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,file to be served from the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.66,0:27:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,.well-known standard directory
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.60,0:27:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,at the root of her web server.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.24,0:27:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You could also serve this file
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.59,0:27:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,from the root of the web server,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.70,0:27:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but the well-known directory is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.03,0:27:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,preferred.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.98,0:27:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And if this linkage doesn't work
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.65,0:27:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the first time that you try it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.38,0:27:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,if you build and run your app
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.29,0:27:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're not seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.13,0:27:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,credentials showing up on the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.34,0:27:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,QuickType bar, we have a few
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.24,0:27:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,steps for you to help the bug.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.81,0:27:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The SWCD daemon will log
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.58,0:27:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,information about making
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.84,0:27:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,requests for setting up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.52,0:27:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,associations between your app
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.98,0:27:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and website on your device every
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.46,0:27:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,time that you build and run your
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.70,0:27:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.81,0:28:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So if something's not working,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.32,0:28:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,plug your device in, open up
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.38,0:28:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Console, and select the device
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.00,0:28:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in the side bar and look for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.39,0:28:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,logging from SWCD.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.59,0:28:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,On the slide right now you can
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.94,0:28:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,see what happens when I
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.83,0:28:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,accidentally put
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.16,0:28:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong.example.com as my
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.54,0:28:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,associated domain inside of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.14,0:28:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.10,0:28:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't able to find an
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.08,0:28:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple-App-Site-Association file.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.06,0:28:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But as soon as I corrected that
