Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.55,0:28:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,directly on the QuickType bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.32,0:28:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And at this point you pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.04,0:28:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,much have all of the information
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.89,0:28:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that you need to know to make
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.42,0:28:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Password AutoFill work really
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.44,0:28:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,well in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.31,0:28:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hoping that this is one of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.55,0:28:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the easiest to adopt features
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.37,0:28:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've ever wanted to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.43,0:28:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,adopt.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.02,0:28:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we wrap things up, I
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.96,0:29:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,just want to quickly touch on a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.09,0:29:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,few related topics to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.23,0:29:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,authentication and passwords,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.38,0:29:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because since you're here,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.17,0:29:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you're probably interested in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.35,0:29:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.01,0:29:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first is about viewing,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.82,0:29:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,saving, and adding new passwords
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.97,0:29:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,on iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.27,0:29:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So besides Password AutoFill, we
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.13,0:29:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,made another change related to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.79,0:29:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,iCloud Keychain this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.33,0:29:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was to move the list of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.84,0:29:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords that you could find in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.15,0:29:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Settings up to a more prominent
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.16,0:29:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,location at the top level called
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.14,0:29:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Accounts and Passwords.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.13,0:29:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside of that section, users
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.01,0:29:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,will be able to authenticate
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.35,0:29:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,with Touch ID, of course, to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.83,0:29:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,view a list of their safe
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.24,0:29:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords, and add new
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.70,0:29:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.57,0:29:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, after all of you have
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.17,0:29:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,adopted Password AutoFill in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.57,0:29:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps, users aren't going to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.27,0:29:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,have a ton of reasons to come in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.84,0:29:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,here to copy and paste passwords
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.45,0:29:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.78,0:29:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But it can still be useful to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.82,0:29:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,look up a password if you need
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.44,0:29:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to enter it on a friend's device
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.00,0:29:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,where you don't have your iCloud
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.10,0:29:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Keychain.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.12,0:30:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, this whole time we've been
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.71,0:30:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about a specific type of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.23,0:30:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,authentication, where your app
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.55,0:30:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and your website, they're the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.87,0:30:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,same entity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.68,0:30:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You're logging into a service
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.85,0:30:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that you or your company owns.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.51,0:30:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know that there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.24,0:30:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,different type of authentication
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.20,0:30:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that a bunch of you need, which
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.32,0:30:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is to log into a third party
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.79,0:30:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,service like a popular social
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.34,0:30:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,network.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.19,0:30:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS's solution for
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.27,0:30:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,authenticating against a social
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.05,0:30:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,network using a technique like
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.45,0:30:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,o-Off is Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.44,0:30:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason for that is that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.15,0:30:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View controller has
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.37,0:30:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari's AutoFill feature, which
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.19,0:30:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,makes it really easy to get
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.23,0:30:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,logged in.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.51,0:30:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, Safari View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.44,0:30:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is sandboxed away from the third
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.50,0:30:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,party app, which gives the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.71,0:30:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,service that's being
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.49,0:30:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,authenticated to a sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.19,0:30:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,guarantee about the security of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.80,0:30:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the passwords.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.14,0:30:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11 Safari View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.50,0:30:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,has been revamped.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.20,0:30:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a new look that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.08,0:30:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,customize to make it feel more
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.93,0:30:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,like part of your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.34,0:31:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you're seeing a demo app
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.43,0:31:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,presenting a Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.46,0:31:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller tinted blue and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.94,0:31:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,white.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.58,0:31:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look very much like
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.51,0:31:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.97,0:31:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like the app itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.01,0:31:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And what this app has also done
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.48,0:31:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is change the top left corner
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.97,0:31:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,button of the Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.25,0:31:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller to say Cancel instead
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.13,0:31:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of Done.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.44,0:31:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.40,0:31:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller is being used for
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.76,0:31:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,authentication, dismissing the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.67,0:31:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.74,0:31:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,cancelling the action of logging
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.54,0:31:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.09,0:31:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not actually successfully
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.27,0:31:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,finishing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.03,0:31:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So Done doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.42,0:31:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To learn about even more
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.62,0:31:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,customizations to Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.57,0:31:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller, and how to implement
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.14,0:31:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,what I just showed you, you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.45,0:31:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,should definitely check out the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.55,0:31:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,session tomorrow at 10 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.47,0:31:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What's New in Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.83,0:31:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.82,0:31:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you want to learn more
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.83,0:31:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,information about implementing
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.64,0:31:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,an o-OFF flow yourself using
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.38,0:31:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.39,0:31:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,go back to the 2015 session
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.11,0:31:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Introducing Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.18,0:31:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.84,0:31:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You might not even be
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.77,0:31:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,implementing a Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.82,0:31:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller yourself to do o-Off,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.79,0:31:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it might actually come for free
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.25,0:32:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as part of an SDK you're using
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.67,0:32:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for authentication.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.49,0:32:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's worth knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.28,0:32:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.38,0:32:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about everything that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.87,0:32:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we've covered so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.70,0:32:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Friction when logging in can
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.92,0:32:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,lead users to abandoning your
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.34,0:32:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.06,0:32:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And we don't want that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.98,0:32:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Your apps are awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.88,0:32:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We want users to use them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.06,0:32:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But fortunately in iOS 11,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.16,0:32:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Password AutoFill is there to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.49,0:32:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,help.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.53,0:32:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And Password AutoFill uses
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.05,0:32:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,heuristics to work automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.45,0:32:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in many of your apps without you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.11,0:32:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,having to make any changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.87,0:32:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But to give your users the best
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.27,0:32:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, and to guarantee
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.18,0:32:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that it works now and in the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.79,0:32:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,future, you can take a few
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.74,0:32:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,simple steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.58,0:32:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is to install one of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.39,0:32:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the betas on your phone and run
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.01,0:32:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,your app and see what your
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.26,0:32:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,starting place is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.42,0:32:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,From there, you can adopt the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.08,0:32:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,username and password text
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.81,0:32:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,content types.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.38,0:32:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That will guarantee that even if
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.43,0:32:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS or your view hierarchy
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.09,0:32:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,changes a few years from now
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.82,0:33:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Password AutoFill will still be
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.12,0:33:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,offered.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.16,0:33:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you take three minutes to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.31,0:33:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,do this now, you might save
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.90,0:33:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself a bug a few years from
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.14,0:33:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.85,0:33:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And then finally, by adopting
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.85,0:33:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the webcredentials Associated
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.49,0:33:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Domain service you can set up a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.59,0:33:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,tight two-way link between your
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.69,0:33:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,app and your website.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.52,0:33:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And that will enable iOS to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.44,0:33:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,offer the exact right
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.57,0:33:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,credentials that your users are
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.20,0:33:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for, that they've
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.42,0:33:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,already saved in Safari and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.83,0:33:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,iCloud Keychain directly on the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.62,0:33:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard in your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.42,0:33:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you run into any issues
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.47,0:33:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,adopting Password AutoFill this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.06,0:33:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,summer, and you can't fix them
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.34,0:33:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,by taking one of the steps that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.82,0:33:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I just outlined, please send us
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.93,0:33:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.56,0:33:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Please file bugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.33,0:33:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We need your help to make sure
